CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 15, 1956, pg. 19, reads: "Rough Sparring Mates Rounding Jackson, Baker Into Top Shape - Time for Work - Bob Baker, left photo, and Hurricane Jackson display different emotions as they put on the gloves prior to working out at Rainbow Gardens in preparation for their Sept. 26 bout at Forbes Field... Jackson, on the other hand, appears as though he's plenty happy with the drill coming up. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of boxer Hurricane Jackson, posed with raised fists in boxing ring at Rainbow Gardens, McKeesport
